Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on rock surface, showing at least four human figures, one dog and numerous unidentified animals. All figures upright and incised in outline. Human figures are to upper right, stick-figure-style, with straight torsos and arms bowed out as if hands on hips, face on. Dog figure is central, naturalistic and facing left with curled tail. To left are numerous very schematic animal figures in outline, unidentified, overlapping one another. A 10cm scale has been fitted at the bottom of the image. New Kalabsha, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
